Commentary: skids on and strikes him on the pad. Rizwan, backing away to access the off side, is badly cramped and takes it on the thigh.
Commentary_short: Santner to Mohammad Rizwan, no run

Commentary: so close to being bowled! Again, it's Santner targeting the stumps, sliding the ball through with the arm with the seam bolt upright. So clearly he doesn't want it to spin, but maybe swing a bit. Rizwan is out with another make-room cut shot and gets an inside edge for four to fine leg
Commentary_short: Santner to Mohammad Rizwan, FOUR runs

Commentary: touch slower through the air, and short enough for Rizwan to rock back and pull to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Santner to Mohammad Rizwan, 2 runs

Commentary: rapid delivery targeting the top of off stump, Rizwan is ready for it this time, as he cuts into the covers, with a straighter bat
Commentary_short: Santner to Mohammad Rizwan, no run

Commentary: hint of turn on the full ball which Rizwan adjusts to very well, opening the face of the bat and blocking it towards point
Commentary_short: Santner to Mohammad Rizwan, no run

Commentary: carts a short ball on middle and leg away to deep square leg
Commentary_short: Santner to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run

Commentary: flies to his left, looking to grab a one-handed stunner but it just evades him! A firmly struck drive from Rizwan beats the bowler's athletic effort and goes to mid-off
Commentary_short: Duffy to Mohammad Rizwan, no run

Commentary: cuts the back of a length ball outside off behind point
Commentary_short: Duffy to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run

Commentary: beats the edge. This is what Duffy is known for. Hitting the deck and getting movement. Eden Park is normally bouncy so it looks really good, flying past Shafiq and through to the keeper
Commentary_short: Duffy to Abdullah Shafique, no run

Commentary: taken at mid-on! Duffy strikes in his first over!. Comes off the pitch just a little slower than he expects, but just the tiniest bit of extra bounce! And as a result, the flick shot, that he means to hit more or less along the ground through midwicket, pops up in the air much much straighter. Great start for the rookie!
Commentary_short: Duffy to Abdullah Shafique, OUT
Dismissal_text: Abdullah Shafique c Chapman b Duffy 0 (5m 2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: defends a fuller delivery on off stump
Commentary_short: Duffy to Haider Ali, no run

Commentary: cracks it over third man! That's how you gotta play here. Short boundaries. Throw the bat at it. Rizwan gets a thick edge to a wide ball and it carries to the fence
Commentary_short: Duffy to Mohammad Rizwan, FOUR runs

Commentary: just over point! Pakistan living very very dangerously. And it's extra bounce again! Haider Ali is not ready for the back of a length ball rearing at him. Takes the shoulder of his bat as he tries to defend, all squared up, and it flies to Phillips, who leaps up, sticks his left hand out and behind him, but the ball lands beyond his reach
Commentary_short: Kuggeleijn to Haider Ali, 1 run

Commentary: hits the deck and gets it to climb up towards Rizwan's chest. He knocks it down by his feet
Commentary_short: Kuggeleijn to Mohammad Rizwan, no run

Commentary: when it's full, it comes onto the bat a little slower. when it's short, it seems to hurry them. This one's full and Rizwan, trying to drive through the line, sees his bat turn in his hand and the mis-hit to mid-off gets only one. He was looking to access the gap at extra cover
Commentary_short: Kuggeleijn to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run

Commentary: flies through as he hits the deck again. Haider is a shot-maker. He sees one he can get under and goes for the slog. Misses
Commentary_short: Kuggeleijn to Haider Ali, no run

Commentary: beats him with a gorgeous ball, back of a length on off stump, and straightening past the outside edge. This is tough stuff out there.
Commentary_short: Kuggeleijn to Haider Ali, no run

Commentary: launches it over midwicket. Haider's shots are usually jaw dropping. This one isn't quite as well timed, but the ferocious intent behind it, is something to see. Bowl length to him at your peril!
Commentary_short: Kuggeleijn to Haider Ali, 2 runs

Commentary: pushes outside off stump, but the fuller ball decks past his reach. Duffy draws seam movement away from the bat again
Commentary_short: Duffy to Mohammad Rizwan, no run

Commentary: lovely shot! All he has to do is give it direction. And he does. A full ball on leg stump is lifted to the fine leg boundary with a touch of class!
Commentary_short: Duffy to Mohammad Rizwan, FOUR runs

Commentary: blocks a good length ball on middle
Commentary_short: Duffy to Mohammad Rizwan, no run

Commentary: dropped by the bowler! It's a tough chance, demanding that he go the wrong way to his follow through and dive to his right. Again, the ball seems to hold up just a bit when it's pitched up and Rizwan, looking to drive down the ground and on the up, is nearly done.
Commentary_short: Duffy to Mohammad Rizwan, no run

Commentary: taken by one of two short covers! Oh this is great bowling. This is a sign of a domestic player in top form. Duffy captains Otago. He's been around for years and years. And the moment he sees a batsman charging at him, he drags his line wide, hiding the ball from his reach. Rizwan still tries to reach for the ball and only toe-ends it to the straighter fielder Phillips
Commentary_short: Duffy to Mohammad Rizwan, OUT
Dismissal_text: Mohammad Rizwan c Phillips b Duffy 17 (16m 17b 3x4 0x6) SR: 100.00

Commentary: taken at mid-on! Eish! He's skittish against the bounce. But he goes for the pull nonetheless. The fact that he hasn't put everything into the shot is apparent in how the ball floats down the ground. Terrible mis-hit. Comes off almost the splice of the bat. And is easily taken by a backtracking Chapman
Commentary_short: Duffy to Mohammad Hafeez, OUT
Dismissal_text: Mohammad Hafeez c Chapman b Duffy 0 (1m 1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: Extra bounce! Extra bounce!They can't handle the extra bounce! Haider is looking to whip a back of a length ball through the leg side. But in addition to the ball coming up at a height he doesn't expect, it also doesn't come on to his bat. All of that means he gets a leading edge which the bowler himself runs up and takes. Spectacular spell of bowling by New Zealand. They really are very good at understanding conditions and exploiting them at double quick time.
Commentary_short: Kuggeleijn to Haider Ali, OUT
Dismissal_text: Haider Ali c & b Kuggeleijn 3 (14m 5b 0x4 0x6) SR: 60.00

Commentary: back of a length and outside off, pushes into the covers
Commentary_short: Kuggeleijn to Khushdil Shah, no run

Commentary: full and outside off, Shah tries to smear it through the covers, but a hint of inswing gets his inside edge
Commentary_short: Kuggeleijn to Khushdil Shah, no run

Commentary: full and outside off, eases it to mid-off
Commentary_short: Kuggeleijn to Khushdil Shah, no run

Commentary: lovely batting! Shah waits for the ball, he waits for it to get as high up as it would, then he hits it on top of that bounce and cuts it away to the boundary

Commentary: defends a back of a length ball into the midwicket region to keep the strike. That is the best bit of cricket Pakistan have played so far.

Commentary: full, straight and swinging into the stumps. And once again, Shah shows excellent balance at the crease, waiting for the ball to get under his eyes and flicking it off the middle of the bat through midwicket.

Commentary: shortish and outside off and once again he looks unhurried. Calmly glides it to cover
Commentary_short: Duffy to Khushdil Shah, no run

Commentary: looks for the drive on the up, places it to the left of mid-off and sprints through for a single

Commentary: back of a length delivery slips down leg side
Commentary_short: Duffy to Shadab Khan, 1 wide

Commentary: full on middle, Shadab pushes down the pitch
Commentary_short: Duffy to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: gets it to straighten and Shadab is wary of the threat, making sure he steps forward to it and blocks with a very straight, very firm defensive bat
Commentary_short: Duffy to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: looks to nudge the back of a length ball through midwicket, but again it doesn't come onto the bat as well as he expects and Shadab's groan of disappointment tells it all as he watches the ball pop back down the pitch
Commentary_short: Duffy to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: it's short. it's a googly. he rocks back and pulls to deep midwicket

Commentary: inside edge as Shadab is drawn into playing an expansive drive through the off side, but the tossed up legbreak drifts in just enough and dips on him to secure the mis-hit

Commentary: defends a flighted delivery on off stump
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Khushdil Shah, no run

Commentary: stands up tall against a googly outside off and pushes into the covers
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Khushdil Shah, no run

Commentary: slides under the bat this time as Sodhi keeps going googlies against the left-hander. Shah goes to cut and misses
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Khushdil Shah, no run

Commentary: waits nicely on the quicker, shorter ball on off stump and dabs it through point
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Khushdil Shah, 1 run

Commentary: starts with a bouncer from around the wicket. Shah looks to hook it, but it's past him, around head high.
Commentary_short: Tickner to Khushdil Shah, no run

Commentary: full and outside off, he hits to mid-off
Commentary_short: Tickner to Khushdil Shah, no run

Commentary: goes round-arm and as a result the ball strays onto the pads, Shah loves that, flicking it away to the fine leg boundary
Commentary_short: Tickner to Khushdil Shah, FOUR runs

Commentary: carves it to the sweeper! It's full. It's wide. It's inviting and Shah laces it to the Phillips. He's been hitting the middle right from ball one. This game might rest on his shoulders now
Commentary_short: Tickner to Khushdil Shah, 1 run

Commentary: dabs a shortish delivery outside off to third man
Commentary_short: Tickner to Shadab Khan, 1 run

Commentary: drives smoothly down the ground and long-on running to his right picks it up
Commentary_short: Tickner to Khushdil Shah, 1 run

Commentary: rocks back and cuts the googly, but he hits it straight to cover. Either side of him, and it would have been four
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Khushdil Shah, no run

Commentary: taken at point! Oh, the best of them is gone now. And once again, it's the result of an ill-advised shot. The square boundaries at Eden Park are big (enough). That's why Sodhi keeps bowling short and spinning the ball away from the left-hander. Here he ventures a little fuller, specifically to draw the false shot. And he does. A slog sweep to a ball outside off stump. Shah can't drag it and only gets an edge that goes straight up and comes down to settle safely in Guptill's hands

Commentary: pulls to long-on

Commentary: nudges a good length ball on middle through square leg

Commentary: doesn't quite pick the googly and gets an inside edge to a good length ball that is looking to topple his off stump

Commentary: whips a shortish legbreak from outside off to long-on
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Shadab Khan, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length on middle, defends
Commentary_short: Tickner to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: works a fuller ball on off stump through midwicket
Commentary_short: Tickner to Shadab Khan, 1 run

Commentary: looks to glance a back of a length ball to fine leg, but again, with it not coming onto to the bat, he pops it up to where square leg might have been standing

Commentary: punches a shortish delivery outside off to point
Commentary_short: Tickner to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: ooooh myyy gawwwddd!! Jaaaaccooooobb Duffeeeeeeeyyyyy This could have been one THE greatest boundary catches I have EVER seen! Shades of Daniel Vettori in the 2015 World Cup. This could have been even better. He's at deep third man. He's watching an upper cut that is going for six for all money. Shadab has nailed it. But Duffy is not giving up on it. He leaps up, sticks up his right hand, the ball sticks in it, he comes down, slides towards the boundary, and as he does so, the tip of his finger in his left hand brushes against the advertising triangles and robs the world of one of the most amazing catches ever.

Commentary: looks for another upper cut, but this time Shadab is beaten for pace and bounce

Commentary: gets a single to the onside

Commentary: defended
Commentary_short: Santner to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: darted through, flicked to the onside. They think about a run but the field is too tight

Commentary: he's really zipping that through with little flight. Shadab uses his feet to squeeze a single through the offside

Commentary: driven straight back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Santner to Imad Wasim, no run

Commentary: worked down to long-on and Imad gets himself off strike

Commentary: fuller, less flight, and paddled down to fine leg for a single
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Shadab Khan, 1 run

Commentary_short: Sodhi to Imad Wasim, 1 run

Commentary: that's not the best delivery, and Shadab cashes in! Zipped through on his pads, sat up nicely and he helps it above the man in the circle at fine leg for four. Finally a big over for Pakistan; they need many, many more of those

Commentary: opens the face and runs down to the man at 45

Commentary: slightly wider, cut away and the pair exchange ends

Commentary: loose delivery, there to be hit. Darted in and got a half-volley, which he dispatches adeptly through extra for a boundary
Commentary_short: Santner to Imad Wasim, FOUR runs
Santner to Imad Wasim, 1 run

Commentary: gave that one more air, and Shadab was a little uncertain about his footwork. Strong finish to the over
Commentary_short: Santner to Shadab Khan, no run

Commentary: Imad greets him with a brilliantly worked cut shot behind backward point. Decent shot to squeeze that between both the ring and boundary fielder. Wasn't all that much width on offer there either

Commentary: full and straight, and Imad drives down to long-off for one

Commentary: greets him with a 138kph short delivery that he got nowhere near. Tried to pull it away but wasn't in the same post code

Commentary: might be the worst delivery of the innings that. Dragged it down, and Shadab had time to put the kettle on before setting up and clobbering it over square leg for a big six
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Shadab Khan, SIX runs

Commentary: gets on the back foot and slashes it away to sweeper cover
Commentary_short: Sodhi to Shadab Khan, 1 run

Commentary: wrong'un, driven down to long-off

Commentary: nicely cut away, beats the point fielder and has time to come back for two

Commentary: straight to the fielder, but even so, 16 off the over. Pakistan will be looking to finish strongly now

Commentary: cramps him for room from around the wicket, driven back to him

Commentary: fill and claps him on the pads. New Zealand appeal, and even review, though it's clear to every man and his dog, surely, that that pitched outside leg. And the review confirms it

Commentary: darted into Faheem, gets an inside edge. Tight over so far
Commentary_short: Santner to Faheem Ashraf, no run

Commentary: claps him on the pads again, Faheem can't quite work him out
Commentary_short: Santner to Faheem Ashraf, no run

Commentary: and gets a single to prevent the maiden, but what an over that's been from Santner. Made up for Sodhi's sloppiness in the previous one

Commentary: Tickner begins with a wide down legside. Good pace though, touching 140, and Faheem hasn't really got going yet

Commentary: good batting, drops it dead and gets Shadab back on strike

Commentary: squired away down to third man and they come back for a couple. Shadab's batting intelligently but he'll continue to need support from the other end

Commentary: just short of a length, played on the up over cover and down to the sweeper

Commentary: bit sloppy from Tickner, Faheem was looking to help it over fine leg

Commentary: leg stump line, and all Faheem can do is get a legbye and get Shadab back on for the last couple of deliveries

Commentary: slower ball, Shadab lets out a grunt of frustration as he fails to middle. The slash to cover only fetches him one

Commentary: well that's put a cheery tune on the over for Pakistan. Short and sat up for Faheem Ashraf, right in his arc. That's perhaps the shot he plays best, as he gets in line and lofts it over square leg for a six

Commentary: Sodhi makes amends! What a superb catch that is, and Duffy's fantasy evening continues! It wasn't the best delivery, in truth, down leg side from around the wicket. But Shadab got a top edge that hovered in the atmosphere around the man at 45. Sodhi had to run backwards and put in the dive, but he got the job done. Lethal blow to the solar plexus of Pakistan's hopes

Commentary: takes the pace off it, and Faheem guides it down to third man. NZ won't mind putting Wahab on strike

Commentary: he didn't mean that, but ask him if he cares! Short and Wahab pulled and hoped for the best. The sheer pace on the delivery took it over the keeper's head and straight down to the boundary for six

Commentary: another ungainly pull, not the prettiest, but gets Faheem on strike

Commentary: what an exquisite shot that is! Almost like he brushed the back of the ball and caresses it over extra cover al the way for six. That was an oil painting of a cricket shot

Commentary: and follows it up with another six! That might have taken the sheen off Duffy's evening a little bit. Poor delivery dragged down leg side and he helps it down to fine leg for another maximum! 20 off the over

Commentary_short: Kuggeleijn to Wahab Riaz, no run

Commentary: and finally Wahab's luck runs outHe'd been swinging, as they say, like a rusty gate, and this time a thick edge carries down to long-ff for a straightforward catch. Kuggeleijn gets his third

Commentary: this time ensures he doesn't have any room. Faheem can only drive back at him, but a misfield allows them to take a single

Commentary: lovely finish to the over. Yorker that Shaheen digs out brilliantly. Keeps the strike, which I'm not sure Pkaistan will have wanted

Commentary: short and Haris swings without getting close to it. They run the bye, and Pakistan finish with 152 This is probably below par, but from 20/4, you bet Pakistan will walk off somewhat relieved. They got a little bit of momentum in that onslaught from Shadab and Faheem at the end, and with their bowling line-up, they may just make it tricky for New Zealand. join us in about 15 minutes to see how New Zealand go

Commentary: strikes him high on the thigh as he pitches it on a good length and gets it to nip in off middle stump. Guptill, looking to nudge it towards mid-on, doesn't connect

Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Guptill, no run

Commentary: knocks a back of a length ball on leg stump to midwicket
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Guptill, no run

Commentary: allows the short ball on off stump to come to him and gently taps it in front and to the right of point. Lovely shot for a well judged single.

Commentary: kisses the pad and goes through to the keeper as Guptill tries a flick. Shadab is looking for inputs on whether to go for a review, someone wisely says no.

Commentary: good stuff. You need to play Imad with a straight bat and Seifert does, stepping forward and pushing to long-off

Commentary: blocks a full ball angling into leg stump

Commentary: stops on the pitch does this short and wide ball, ruining Guptill's timing as he goes for a cut

Commentary: nails the cut this time. There's a little bit of width on this. There's plenty of pace. So Guptill shifts his weight back and finds the gap behind point

Commentary: quicker, flatter and tighter on middle. Guptill is ready for it, nudging a single through midwicket

Commentary: goes back to block a shortish ball to the right of the pitch, looking for a single. Eventually they decide not to go for it with Imad racing for the ball
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Seifert, no run

Commentary: oooh hooo hooo. This is a supremely good catch. This is Shadab Khan at his absolute, shining, pristine, beautiful best! Running back from mid-off at FULL speed. Tracking a big hit down the ground - that when they come off Martin Guptill's bat usually go for six - but Shadab doesn't let up. He keeps his eyes on it - which is so hard because he has to look over his left shoulder. He realises it might beat him at the last minute and so dives headlong after the ball, reaching out both hands, and he takes it so very cleanly. Such a difficult catch and he made it look as if it was destined to be out. Pakistan have their early wicket. They become a far more terrifying bowling side now.
